<item>
            <title>[LU-17098] sanity-pcc uses wrong uid / gid and fails when uidmap is missing</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17098</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;While debugging another patch I was running sanity-pcc.sh to see which test pass / fail. A few fail due to assuming uid = 500 and gid = 1000. This is wrong. Also one of the sanity-pcc test fails due to uidmap missing in the install for Ubuntu 22.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Ubuntu 22 clients running latest master.</environment>
